{
  "text": "Animals. Mice were housed under a 12 h light/dark cycle with free access to food and water. The Animal Care and Use Committees of St. Jude Children's Research Hospital approved all of the protocols performed in this study and the methods were carried out in accordance with the approved guidelines. Sox2-CreER mice were generously provided by Konrad Hochedlinger, Harvard University, and are now available from Jackson Laboratory (Stock #017593). The mT/mG (Stock# 007576) mice were purchased from The Jackson Laboratory. Genotyping of Sox2-CreER and mT/mG mice were previously described [CITATION_1] 54 .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "205243365"
